.\" termin.al-name: tail
.\" termin.al-usage: tail [-n count] <path>
.\" termin.al-summary: Print final raw document lines.
.TH TAIL 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
tail \- Print final raw document lines.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
tail [-n count] <path>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Prints the last requested lines of one virtual document. The document is read as raw text rather than rendered Markdown.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B -n count
Print count final lines. Count must be a supported positive integer.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ tail -n 3 about.md
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
help(1), man(1)
